title: What's been said on social media, Jan. 12
snippet:
BEIJING, Jan. 12 (Xinhua) -- The following is a selection of the latest posts on social media.


 Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (@PTIofficial on Twitter)
body:
As a consequent PM Imran Khan's visit to China in November 2018 and a follow up meeting with the Chinese Ambassador by @UdarOfficial, Special Assistant to the Prime Minister on Youth Affairs (Usman Dar), China - Pakistan Youth Communication Committee is being established


 - - - -


 The Association of Southeast Asian Nations (@ASEAN on Twitter)


 #ASEAN and China will launch the ASEAN-China Year of Media Exchanges 2019 in Jakarta on Jan. 14. The event will coincide with the Mission of China to ASEAN's launch of "Dan's Way", a unique documentary focusing on China-ASEAN cultural exchange and cooperation.


 - - - -


 UAE Foreign Minister Anwar Gargash (@AnwarGargash on Twitter)


 Stockholm Agreement in peril. Since start of #Hodeidah ceasefire, Houthis committed 464 recorded violations & broke commitments by not withdrawing from port.

Brazen attempt to derail the political process of @OSE_Yemen (UN Office of the Special Envoy of the Secretary-General for Yemen).

Enditem
